This paper is about the optimization of neural networks, which is a core topic in machine learning. The paper specifically addresses the issue of sub-optimal local minima in over-parameterized neural networks, which is a problem that falls under the category of deep learning and neural networks (cs.LG). The paper also discusses the role of activation functions and data samples, which are important topics in neural network optimization (cs.NE). Additionally, the paper mentions the use of neural networks in computer vision (cs.CV) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI), which are related sub-fields of machine learning. Finally, the paper uses optimization analysis, which is a fundamental tool in data science (cs.DS).
